      "content": "i get the advertising thing, but it feels way too specific for just \"improving experience.\" it's like they're testing how the environment can influence me or something. like, if they see a certain light pattern makes me more impulsive or easier to sell things to, wouldn't they want to perfect that? it feels less like they're watching me for ads and more like they're actively running some kind of psychological experiment on my house.",
